.TH ilrun 1 "Viper" "viper-ilrun" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ilrun \- Run a Viper IL program
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ilrun
[\fIoptions\fR] \fIFILE.il\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBilrun\fR is a user-friendly wrapper for executing textual Viper IL files that define a \fCfunc @main()\fR entry point. It mirrors the \fBviper -run\fR engine but with simpler syntax.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--trace\fR[=\fIil\fR|\fIsrc\fR]
Enable execution tracing at IL or source level.
.TP
\fB--stdin-from\fR \fIFILE\fR
Redirect program stdin from file.
.TP
\fB--max-steps\fR \fIN\fR
Limit total instructions executed; 0 disables the limit.
.TP
\fB--bounds-checks\fR
Enable runtime array bounds checks.
.TP
\fB--break\fR \fILABEL\fR|\fIFILE:LINE\fR
Set a breakpoint by IL label or source location.
.TP
\fB--break-src\fR \fIFILE:LINE\fR
Set a source breakpoint.
.TP
\fB--watch\fR \fINAME\fR
Watch a variable and log stores.
.TP
\fB--count\fR
Show per-opcode execution counts.
.TP
\fB--time\fR
Show wall-clock runtime.
.TP
\fB--dump-trap\fR
Show detailed trap diagnostics.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Display help and exit.
.TP
\fB--version\fR
Print version and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
Run with tracing and a breakpoint at source line 10:
.nf
ilrun program.il --trace --break-src main.bas:10
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success; non-zero on error.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBviper\fR(1), \fBil-verify\fR(1)

